captions.text:
It's Brooklyn and
Bailey and today we

are doing a new kind of video
called Thrift Store Fashion.

-We thought it would be
fun to go to thrift stores

to show you guys that you can
find cute and cheap outfits.

-We'll begin by showing you
guys some of the outfits

that we found at
the thrift stores.

It's Bailey and for
my first outfit,

we have these
adorable purple polka

dot skinny jeans, along with
these wonderful brown wedge

And then we have this
cute brown braided belt

and this yellow floral shirt
that I that just rolled

And then I also have this
Egyptian-style bracelet
that I've put up on my forearm.

And for my first outfit, I
chose a comfy, cosy outfit.

I've got these grey Navajo print
leggings and this green knitted

-And for my second
outfit, I decided
to go for a more dressy look.

To start off, we have a green
ruffled skirt with floral print

that matches perfectly
with my white lace blouse.

And then I have a tan handbag
and these adorable brown wedge

-And I have another
comfy, cosy outfit.

I've got this blue and white
baseball tee over grey jeans

and a cute owl necklace
that's in there somewhere,

-And for my third outfit, I
decided to go a little bit more

I just paired my white lace
blouse and my brown heels

with some adorable skinny jeans
and his leopard floppy hat,

which makes this
outfit even cheaper

because I paired it with
some stuff we already have.
I hope you guys enjoyed it.

Don't forget to leave a
comment below on which

outfit you guys like the
best and also don't forget

Are you ready to
have the fan off?

We should just go like
this in our video.
